Sulawesifulvius thailandicus is most similar to Sulawesifulvius schuhi and Sulawesifulvius yinggelingensis in having large red markings on the dorsal surface (Figs 2-3, 20, 23; Mu and Liu 2014 ) (only slightly tinged with red in Sulawesifulvius indicus ) (
Yeshwanth and Cherot 2015
). Sulawesifulvius thailandicus can, however, be easily distinguished by the characteristic shape of the parameres (as depicted in Figs 14-17) and the endosoma with three endosomal sclerites (Fig. 13).
